We need to prove that the matchable sets of a graph $G$ form the independent sets of a matroid, and that this matroid has rank $2\nu(G)$, where $\nu(G)$ is the size of the maximum matching in $G$. Additionally, we need to show that if every vertex of $G$ is not in some maximum matching, then the matchable sets matroid has no coloops and every pair of adjacent vertices is a series pair.

