A **series pair** is a pair of elements that are in every dependent set. In our case, adjacent vertices $x, y$ form a series pair if in every matching $M$ that matches $x$, $y$ must also be matched by $M$, or vice versa. The hypothesis that for every vertex $v$, there is a maximum matching not containing $v$ implies that any pair of adjacent vertices must be a series pair in the matroid.

